# bad_hosts
# =========
# One Perl regular expression per line, matched against the posting host or
# injection host extracted by Cleanfeed.  Confirm the exact extracted value in
# audit logs before enabling a rule; it may differ from the first visible host
# in Path.
#
# Exact hostname:
# ^reader23\.abusive-provider\.example$
#
# Any numbered reader in one domain:
# ^reader[0-9]+\.abusive-provider\.example$
#
# Readers 10 through 29 only:
# ^reader(?:1[0-9]|2[0-9])\.abusive-provider\.example$
#
# Two exact hosts:
# ^(?:reader7|reader19)\.example\.net$
#
# IPv4 documentation range 192.0.2.16 through 192.0.2.31:
# ^192\.0\.2\.(?:1[6-9]|2[0-9]|3[01])$
#
# One exact IPv6 address.  Colons are literal in Perl regexes:
# ^2001:db8:1234::42$
#
# One documented IPv6 prefix.  Anchor the beginning but intentionally permit
# the remaining host bits:
# ^2001:db8:1234:
#
# Avoid blocking a whole commercial provider because of one abusive account.
# Prefer the smallest stable hostname/address range supported by evidence.
